        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">According to the report "Methanol fuel in China 2020, China Association of Alcohol and Ether Fuel and Automobiles (CAAEFA), 2021" Chian is one of the largest methanol producer and consumer worldwide. Namely, statistics from CNFIA, in 2019, report that a total methanol consumption of 80 Mt (including imports of 10 Mt), and a production oif 69.9 Mt.

At the same time, around about two-thirds of China's methanol feedstock is generated from coal, while the residual production is covered from coking gas and natural gas (eia, 2017) .

Moreover, China, as the largest methanol producer, accounted for 57% of the worlds production (iea, 2022).

Finally, according to NETL, "About 55-65% of global methanol production uses natural gas feedstock, about 30-35% uses coal, with the rest using coking gas and other feedstocks. (Alvarado M. Methanol Industry Overview, 35th World Methanol Conference, Berlin, Germany 2017). In 2021, worldwide methanol production reached 107 million metric tons."

All of the above were used in the Mathematica Relation to estimate the production volume of methanol, from coal, in China.

References:
https://www.methanol.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/China-Methanol-Fuel-Report-2020_final-1.pdf, last accessed 28-07-2023.
IEA (2022), Chemicals, IEA, Paris https://www.iea.org/reports/chemicals, License: CC BY 4.0
https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=30072#:~:text=About%20two%2Dthirds%20of%20China's,using%20coal%20as%20a%20feedstock., last accessed 28-07-2023.
https://www.netl.doe.gov/research/carbon-management/energy-systems/gasification/gasifipedia/methanol#:~:text=About%2055%2D65%25%20of%20global,reached%20107%20million%20metric%20tons., last accessed 28-07-2023.

</productionVolumeComment>
