      <intermediateExchange id="360dd349-6083-54cc-86a1-a514bde3a3c8" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="BP_ash" amount="-0.16" isCalculatedAmount="false" intermediateExchangeId="76ab0018-e176-43e0-b42c-12e82b937fef" activityLinkId="8c6172e4-152d-5a6b-8f6f-69944ed0ed05" productionVolumeMathematicalRelation=" RP_PV * ( BP_ash / RP )">
        <name xml:lang="en">hard coal ash</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Value reported by Liu, Yigang, et al. "Comprehensive analysis of environmental impacts and energy consumption of biomass-to-methanol and coal-to-methanol via life cycle assessment." Energy 204 (2020): 117961" for the production of methanol via coal gasification.
The amount of ash output accounts for 10.5% of the input anthracite (hard coal). In general, the chemical composition of anthracite comprise of around 77% carbon, 6-16% ash, and moister. Some trace elements are also present in the chemical composition of anthracite, such as sulfur - 0.23-1.2%, silica oxide - 2.2-5.4%, alumina - 2%, ferric oxide - 0.4%. Reference: Wypych, George. "Fillers-Origin, chemical composition, properties, and morphology." Handbook of Fillers 4 (266) (2016): 13.</comment>
